The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically finding a matching between two sets of points in the plane with non-crossing line segments. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also uses combinatorial and graph theoretic techniques to solve the problem, which could place it in the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of group theory and symmetry to simplify the problem, which could place it in the categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
